b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Kapwing AI is best suited for content teams collaborating on video, quick social media edits, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Pictory, meanwhile, shines for marketers repurposing long form content, social media clips, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Kapwing AI describes itself as \"Collaborative AI video editor for content teams.\" Pictory, established in 2020, positions itself as \"Automatically create short branded videos from long content.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Pictory** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (6 vs 3), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Kapwing AI is a poor choice — far from it. Kapwing AI excels in its own right, particularly for content teams collaborating on video and quick social media edits.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value great long-to-short conversion, go with Pictory. If browser-based, no install matters more to you, Kapwing AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
